# Migration Spec

## Scope

Idempotent PostgreSQL schema/data migrations for all tenant databases.

## Load when

Schema, seed data, model fields, indexes, store/auth/session/page tables, or
`grengo migrate` behavior changes.

## Owns

- `backend/internal/migrations/*.sql`
- Fresh schema: `backend/internal/migrations/001_schema.sql`
- Seed data: `backend/internal/migrations/002_seed.sql`
- Migration runner invoked by `grengo migrate <name|all>`

## Contracts

- Migrations run in filename sort order.
- There is no migration history table; every SQL file must be safe to re-run.
- Fresh installs must be represented in `001_schema.sql` and `002_seed.sql`.
- Incremental files remain for existing deployments, data movement, compatibility
  bridges, or one-time operational transitions.
- Use `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`, `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS`,
  `CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS`, `ON CONFLICT`, guarded `DO $$` blocks, and
  `IF EXISTS` where needed.
- Prices and monetary rewards are stored as integer cents.

